        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the annotation.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6705F.xml" resp="#automat">letter to J. N. Hegt, 19 April 1869</ref> and n. 1. <hi rend="italic">Pavo cristatus</hi> has a white form. CD cited Hegt for his remarks on the spurs of peafowl in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 290 n. 28.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6705F.xml" resp="#automat">letter to J. N. Hegt, 19 April 1869</ref>; see also <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6699.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Edward Blyth, 17 April 1869</ref>. Hegt refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6879.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Heinrich Bodinus</ref>. There is a draft of this letter in the Municipal Archive at Amsterdam (Gemeentearchief). In the draft, the last sentence of this letter reads: ‘As far as I know there are living specimens of Mandrills in the Cologne gardens D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Bodinus director in the Frankfurt gardens D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4225.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Max Schmidt</ref>, direct. and Antwerp M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Vekemans direct. We have only a very poor Collection of the Common Species of Monkeys.’ The reference is to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6920.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Jacobus Vekemans</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
